    <text>
        <body>
            <pb n="1"/>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <placeName>Lancaster</placeName>
                <date>22 Juny 1857</date>
            </p>
            <p><addressee>Rev. Leeser</addressee>
                <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>.</p>
            <p>
                <add>German?</add>
            </p>
            <pb n="2"/>
            <p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Lancaster</placeName>, <date>June 22, 1857</date></p>
            <p>
                <addressee>Rev Leeser</addressee>
                <placeName>Phila</placeName>
            </p>
            <p>Beloved friend</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">I have happy news today. Yesterday, in the morning,<lb/> my wife
                bore a lusty boy——<add>Hebrew</add>. The Brith will be on <date>Sunday</date><lb/>
                morning. My friend <persName>Newhouse</persName> has been designated as a
                godfather.<lb/> I have invited him <sic>tpday</sic> and made it conditional on his
                bringing<lb/> you with him I want my <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName> friends in
                my house and<lb/> as you are among them <sic>i</sic> request your presence on
                    <date>Sunday</date> with<lb/>
                <persName>Mr Newhouse</persName> and the <sic>rst</sic> of our friends. <sic>i</sic>
                will not accept any<lb/> excuse but count on your presence so that you may help
                to<lb/> increase the joy of the festival.</p>
            <p rend="indent(6)">etc etc</p>
            <p rend="indent(7)">Signed—Your sincere friend</p>
            <p rend="indent(8)">
                <persName role="author">Jacob Herzog</persName>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(6)">I expect you in company with <persName>Mr Bachmann</persName>,
                    <persName>Mr<lb/> Newhouse</persName> and <persName>Mr Spartz</persName>,
                    <persName>Frank S. Cohen</persName></p>
        </body>
    </text>
